setDatatypeRepresentationMap

public void setDatatypeRepresentationMap(javax.xml.namespace.QName[] dtrMapTypes,
                                         javax.xml.namespace.QName[] dtrMapRepresentations)
Description copied from interface: EXIFactory
By default, each typed value in an EXI stream is represented by the associated built-in EXI datatype representation. However, EXI processors MAY provide the capability to specify different built-in EXI datatype representations or user-defined datatype representations for representing specific schema datatypes. This capability is called Datatype Representation Map.

Specified by:
setDatatypeRepresentationMap in interface EXIFactory

setSelfContainedElements

public void setSelfContainedElements(javax.xml.namespace.QName[] scElements)
Description copied from interface: EXIFactory
Self-contained elements may be read independently from the rest of the EXI body, allowing them to be indexed for random access. The "selfContained" element MUST NOT appear in an EXI options document when one of "compression", "pre-compression" or "strict" elements are present in the same options document.

Specified by:
setSelfContainedElements in interface EXIFactory

The blockSize option specifies the block size used for EXI compression. When the "blockSize" element is absent in the EXI Options document, the default blocksize of 1,000,000 is used.

setValueMaxLength

public void setValueMaxLength(int valueMaxLength)
Description copied from interface: EXIFactory
The valueMaxLength option specifies the maximum length of value content items to be considered for addition to the string table. The default value "unbounded" is assumed when the "valueMaxLength" element is absent in the EXI Options document.

See http://www.w3.org/TR/exi/#key-valueMaxLengthOption

Specified by:
setValueMaxLength in interface EXIFactory
Parameters:
valueMaxLength - the maximum string length of value content items to be considered for addition to the string table

See http://www.w3.org/TR/exi/#key-valuePartitionCapacityOption
